plot(SIMS~ARM,data=data)

basicNN <- ggplot(data,aes(y=SIMS,x=ARM))
basicNN + geom_point()

basicNN + geom_point(aes(col=ARM)) 

cor(SIMS~ARM,data=data)
## [1] 0.6860073
model.1 <- lm(SIMS~ARM,data=data)
summary.lm(model.1)
## 
## Call:
## lm(formula = SIMS ~ ARM, data = data)
## 
## Residuals:
##     Min      1Q  Median      3Q     Max 
## -3.6467 -0.7502 -0.0285  0.6875  3.0770 
## 
## Coefficients:
##              Estimate Std. Error t value Pr(>|t|)    
## (Intercept) -4.095160   0.391745  -10.45   <2e-16 ***
## ARM          0.054563   0.004806   11.35   <2e-16 ***
## ---
## Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1
## 
## Residual standard error: 1.226 on 145 degrees of freedom
## Multiple R-squared:  0.4706, Adjusted R-squared:  0.467 
## F-statistic: 128.9 on 1 and 145 DF,  p-value: < 2.2e-16
basicNN + geom_point(aes(col=ARM)) + geom_smooth(method=lm)

x=data.frame(GRIP=94, ARM=88)
predict.lm(model.1,x,interval = "prediction")
##         fit       lwr      upr
## 1 0.7063836 -1.726209 3.138977

The 95% predictions intervals are between .706-3.13

Now for the SIMs the function of ARM+GRIP

plot(SIMS~ARM+GRIP,data=data,xlab="ARM+GRIP")

basicNN <- ggplot(data,aes(y=SIMS,x=ARM+GRIP))
basicNN + geom_point()

basicNN + geom_point(aes(col=ARM+GRIP)) 

cor(SIMS~ARM+GRIP,data=data)
## [1] 0.7326545
model.3 <- lm(SIMS~ARM+GRIP,data=data)
summary.lm(model.3)
## 
## Call:
## lm(formula = SIMS ~ ARM + GRIP, data = data)
## 
## Residuals:
##     Min      1Q  Median      3Q     Max 
## -3.1846 -0.7380 -0.0641  0.7394  2.8634 
## 
## Coefficients:
##              Estimate Std. Error t value Pr(>|t|)    
## (Intercept) -5.433871   0.461815 -11.766  < 2e-16 ***
## ARM          0.037311   0.005774   6.462 1.50e-09 ***
## GRIP         0.024470   0.005158   4.744 4.99e-06 ***
## ---
## Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1
## 
## Residual standard error: 1.144 on 144 degrees of freedom
## Multiple R-squared:  0.5422, Adjusted R-squared:  0.5358 
## F-statistic: 85.26 on 2 and 144 DF,  p-value: < 2.2e-16
basicNN + geom_point(aes(col=ARM+GRIP)) + geom_smooth(method=lm)

x=data.frame(GRIP=94, ARM=88)
predict.lm(model.3,x,interval = "prediction")
##         fit       lwr      upr
## 1 0.1496476 -2.132373 2.431668
a=anova(model.1,model.3)
print(a)

str(a)
## Classes 'anova' and 'data.frame':    2 obs. of  6 variables:
##  $ Res.Df   : num  145 144
##  $ RSS      : num  218 188
##  $ Df       : num  NA 1
##  $ Sum of Sq: num  NA 29.4
##  $ F        : num  NA 22.5
##  $ Pr(>F)   : num  NA 4.99e-06
##  - attr(*, "heading")= chr  "Analysis of Variance Table\n" "Model 1: SIMS ~ ARM\nModel 2: SIMS ~ ARM + GRIP"

\(H_0\) We fail to reject the null hypothesis showing that there is no difference between arm strength vs. arm+grip strength

\(H_A\) We reject the null hypothesis showing that there is a difference between arm strength vs. arm+grip strength

We reject the null hypothesis based on the evidence we have it with a Pvalue of 4.994e-06 which is less than .05 and the model that predicts simulations that uses arm+grip is a better model for the simulations that uses arm only.
